track_notes: Nice hike. RT Totals: 4.7 miles, 850 ft gain.
track_title: Canjilon Mountain RT from Upper Canjilon Lake

track_notes: Hike from road closed sign up the final moraine-like slopes to summit. Mostly moderate with a few steep sections. Approximately a half mile with 480 feet of gain.

From US 84 turn E onto the road to the little town of Canjilon. After reaching Canjilon turn N onto the road to Canjilon Lakes (Cty 280). Follow the initially paved 280 N then NE. At 36.50744, -106.40199, about a quarter mile after 280 turns to dirt, turn NW onto FR 124. Continue on the mostly moderate 124 as it winds northerly for ~ 6.8 miles. At 36.55694, -106.38564 turn N onto a rugged 4WD road that winds NE then E for a bit more than 2 miles towards Canjilon Mountain. Not far below the summit you will run into road closed signs. Although the road continues steeply to the summit, park at the closure and hike the final ~ half mile/480 vertical feet to the top (see Canjilon Western Slopes Hike track).
